The paper deals with algorithmic mechanism design, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that combines computer science, game theory, and economics. The paper specifically focuses on combinatorial public projects, which is a problem in resource allocation. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves designing a polynomial-time algorithm, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper uses matroid rank sums, which are a type of submodular function, and submodularity is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
